==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*waenjan''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[wanian|wānian]]'' (Dutch ''[[wanen]]''), Old High German ''[[wanen|wanēn]]'' (German ''[[wähnen]]''), Old Norse ''[[væna]]'', Gothic [[𐍅𐌴𐌽𐌾𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈwe:nɑn/}}

===Verb===
{{Latinx|'''wēnan'''}} (class 1 weak)

# to [[think]], [[believe]], [[imagine]]
# to [[expect]], [[suspect]], [[hope]]

